 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.8","title":"robot-redesign/validation: add unit tests for SQLite store, projection builder, adapters, attention journal, and incident lifecycle","description":"Add focused package-local unit tests for the runtime data path so the redesign's hardest logic is pinned down before end-to-end coverage is asked to catch it. This task exists because the projection builder, normalization adapters, cursor logic, and incident lifecycle rules contain complex edge behavior that deserves direct tests, not just broad integration runs.","design":"The tests should cover migrations and store APIs, retention decisions, projection recompute behavior, adapter normalization, source_health derivation, degraded-state propagation, watermark handling, replay or resync rules, idempotent retry behavior, request or outcome correlation, duplicate suppression and cooldown or resurfacing rules, operator attention-state persistence and transitions, incident fingerprinting, promotion thresholds, recurrence handling, resolution or reopen behavior, and stable ordering. They should be table-driven, deterministic, and log fixture IDs, request IDs, idempotency keys, cursor values, reason codes, fingerprints, source-health changes, operator-state markers, suppression markers, and assertion diffs with enough detail to root-cause failures quickly.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when the store, projection, adapter, attention, and incident packages each have strong unit coverage for happy-path, boundary, degraded, retry-safe, attention-hygiene, and operator-control conditions, with logging that makes failures actionable instead of cryptic.","notes":"This is the main unit-test bead for the runtime heart of the redesign. Keep the tests close to the packages they validate.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:47:48.913481831Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T01:37:27.302502372Z","source_repo":".","co